git clone: for cloning repo with url to device
git push: save to GH
git pull: get from GH
git commit: commit(tracks) the file with mssg(-m)
git add: can use dot for all or name of the file, moves to staging area
git status: what branch we are in and status
git checkout: to move into another branch (-b for new)
git init: always done at the parent, initialisation of the local dir with git
git branch: lists the branches

